{
    "name": "Genie-Touched Horse",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> warm plains<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or herd (3-10)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Genie-Touched Abilities</b> Each of the four breeds of genie-touched horse (istaheq, misayyah, tuanu, and zefaheen) has three unique genie-touched abilities. In addition, each breed has energy resistance to a specific form of energy and can understand (but cannot speak) one elemental language."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Legends hold that in the distant past, genies gifted certain Keleshite tribes with the companionship of a powerful race of equine mounts. Exactly what these mysterious creatures originally were is now lost to time, but their descendants exist still in the form of four distinct breeds of supernatural steeds known as genietouched horses."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This magnificent creature seems to be a horse, but the sparkle in its eyes reveals its supernatural origins.</i>",
